thread.title: Body discovered in abandoned van in Renton
thread.title_full: Body discovered in abandoned van in Renton | The Seattle Times

author: Sami Edge
title: Body discovered in abandoned van in Renton
text:
Renton police discovered a body inside an abandoned van on Monday morning after a parking-enforcement officer became suspicious of an “unusual odor” coming from the vehicle.
The case is being investigated as a homicide, according to Renton police Cmdr. David Leibman. The body had been decomposing for at least a few days, Liebman said. The gender has not been determined.
According to police, the van was parked on the shoulder of the 100 block of Southwest Victoria Street near Renton Avenue South.
Detectives are investigating.
